[l] Old and busted: Kohlenstoff-Nanoroehren werden die Welt revolutionieren!New hotness: Kohlenstoff-Nanoroehren in den Lungen von Asthma-Kindern gefunden.Nevertheless, there has been some concern over their use after mouse studies showed that injected nanotubes can cause immune reactions similar to those produced by asbestos.To investigate, Fathi Moussa and colleagues at the University of Paris-Saclay, France, studied fluid from the airways of 64 asthmatic children, and discovered carbon nanotubes in all of the samples. Five other children studied also had them in their macrophages – immune cells that clear unwanted particles – taken from the lungs.
